    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because the curriculum was such in Vienna that you-- that a, a teacher that was hired by the, by the [GERMAN], which was like the Jewish Congress here, came in once a week and took all the Jews from one level-- you know, like level three, level four, level five, you know, something like that-- put them all into one class and introduced them, instructed them in the Bible and holidays and Judaism, in general.",
      "word_count": 75
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Uh-- and we were very assimilated, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But-- but-- but there's one thing that I'm going to tell you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If-- if you talk about beliefs-- I was a very tough kid and was a very rowdy kid sometimes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was so much anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
